MASTER CURSOR RUNBOOK — PLUGIN UI TEMPLATE v1
PROJECT: Any new MelechDSP plugin

================================================================
GLOBAL RULES (MANDATORY)
================================================================

You MUST obey all rules defined in 00_SYSTEM_RULES.txt.

This runbook is UI-ONLY.
DO NOT touch:
- DSP
- Engine logic
- Parameter definitions
- Threading / timers
- Performance-critical paths

Minimal diffs.
No cosmetic refactors unless instructed.
STOP after each step.

================================================================
STEP 0 — SESSION INITIALIZATION
================================================================

Context:
This task initializes a new plugin UI using the MelechDSP UI Design System.
Theme / Metrics / Typography are provided by mdsp_ui.

Instructions:
- Treat AnalyzerPro as the reference implementation.
- Copy structure, not visuals.
- Do not invent new UI paradigms.

STOP AFTER DONE

================================================================
STEP 1 — CREATE MAIN VIEW SCAFFOLD
================================================================

TASK:
Create a MainView layout scaffold consistent with AnalyzerPro.

Required structure:
- MainView owns layout only
- Child components own rendering and parameter logic

Expected regions:
- HeaderBar (top)
- FooterBar (bottom)
- Optional Meter rails (left/right)
- Center view (main visualization)
- ControlRail (bottom center)

Rules:
- All layout metrics sourced from ui_.metrics()
- No hardcoded spacing
- No setSize() inside views

Acceptance:
- MainView compiles
- Layout is resizable
- No visual polish required yet

STOP AFTER DONE

================================================================
STEP 2 — UI CONTEXT INJECTION
================================================================

TASK:
Wire mdsp_ui::UiContext through the new plugin UI.

Required actions:
1. PluginEditor owns mdsp_ui::UiContext.
2. MainView receives UiContext by reference.
3. All child UI components receive the same reference.

Rules:
- Single UiContext instance
- No copying Theme or Metrics

Acceptance:
- UI compiles
- Theme + Metrics accessible everywhere

STOP AFTER DONE

================================================================
STEP 3 — PLACEHOLDER VISUALS ONLY
================================================================

TASK:
Use placeholders for visuals until DSP is ready.

Rules:
- Use Grid / Placeholder views
- No heavy drawing logic
- No optimization work

Acceptance:
- UI runs
- Resizes correctly
- No crashes

STOP AFTER DONE

================================================================
END OF RUNBOOK
================================================================